io.smint.clapi.consumer.integration.core.target

Interface ISyncBinaryAsset

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ISyncAsset, ISyncDataType

    public interface ISyncBinaryAsset
extends ISyncAsset
    Represents a Simple Asset containing a single binary asset data.

    Instances implementing this interface are created utilizing one for the factory functions ISyncTarget.createSyncCompoundAsset() or ISyncTarget.createSyncBinaryAsset().

    Two types of assets

    On Smint.io an asset is a unique collection - with a unique ID ISyncAsset.getUuid() - if its meta data (eg: name, description, licenses, restrictions, etc.) and the attached binary data (eg: picture), where each binary data has its own additional Binary ID (see getBinaryUuid()).
    With synchronization targets, the digital binary data is in the center of storing data, as this is what most DAM are using. So synchronization creates a direct mapping between a binary data on the target platform to the binary data on the Smint.io platform, although this is not straight forward as Smint.io uses a different notion of data as its base.

    There are two type of assets in use with Smint.io.

    1. Binary Asset - assets with a single binary attached.
    2. Compound Asset - assets that contain multiple binaries, each being a variant. eg: pictures might be available in various resolutions and dimensions or maybe even localized. Nevertheless all picture have the same image, scene, etc.

    Storage of Binary Asset

    Single Asset can be stored straight forward. Although it might seem unnecessary, it is strongly advised to store the Binary ID (see getBinaryUuid()) with each binary, too.

    Mapping asset IDs between sync target and Smint.io

    Each asset contains a unique ID on the synchronization target (ISyncAsset.getTargetAssetUuid()). Nevertheless the Smint.io platform ID (ISyncAsset.getUuid()) does not address a single binary, and thus each asset on the sync target must store a composite Smint.io key, consisting of Asset ID (ISyncAsset.getUuid()) and Binary ID (getBinaryUuid()). Only this composite key allows a proper mapping of synchronization target IDs and Smint.io binaries. 

     targetAssetUuid == uuid + binaryUuid

    Localized texts with translations

    The texts with translations, the possibly available translations are defined by the value of ISettingsModel.getImportLanguages(). However, not all languages might have a valid translation. Languages without a translation might be omitted. Especially if this is a persistent asset and a new language has been added to the list of languages after storing the asset to the synchronization target, some existing translations might be missing. Such cases are not detected by the synchronization job and unchanged assets will not be updated. Only changes on the Smint.io platform are detected. All changes on the synchronization target are discarded.

    Override of values if part of a Compound Asset (see ISyncCompoundAsset)

    If this asset is part of a Compound Asset and therefore has been retrieved as part of the list from ISyncCompoundAsset.getAssetParts(), its values will override the values of it base compound asset. So, if both received values with something like ISyncAsset.setContentCategory(String), the asset part's value win and should be selected to be stored with the sync target's asset representation.

      • getRecommendedFileName

        String getRecommendedFileName()
        Retrieve the recommended file name to use on the synchronization target.

        Usually the available character set to file names are restricted by the file system storage. So it is not useful to re-use the name of locally download files to determine the name of the binary on the target system. These local file names may contain hashes/IDs and other mechanism to uniquely identify the downloaded asset before uploading it to the target system. Hence the name provided by this function should be used as a base for the file name on the target.

        Returns:
        a valid file name or null if none has been set yet.

        Returns:

      • getDownloadedFile

        File getDownloadedFile()
                throws FileNotFoundException,
                       SmintIoAuthenticatorException
        Downloads and provides the binary file of this Simple Asset.

        Downloading the file happens only once, at the first call to this function. For the actual download, the provider set by setDownloadedFileProvider(Provider) is used. Further calls will return the same downloaded file and bypass the provider - even if the file has been deleted meanwhile.

        Returns:
        a valid file or null if no download provider has been set yet.
        Throws:
        FileNotFoundException - if the file system failed to store the download, thus it can not be found after the download has started. This is also thrown if the download URL is wrong and the file can not be found on the Smint.io platform.
        SmintIoAuthenticatorException - if authentication to the Smint.io API has failed.

      • getBinaryVersion

        int getBinaryVersion()
        Provide the version of the asset's binary file.

        The binary version is used to detect changes on the binary file. Every change will increase the version number. So the newest version will be the one with the highest version number. Nevertheless this one-way synchronization will not sync back any changes to the Smint.io platform.

        Returns:
        usually a positive value but initially 0 if no version has ever been stored/recorded. Must not be a value lower than 0 (negative number) with the only exception that compound assets must return -1 to indicate their compound state.

        Description copied from interface: ISyncAsset
        Sets the Web URL to view the asset on the Smint.io platform in the browser.

      • setLastUpdatedAt

        ISyncBinaryAsset setLastUpdatedAt(OffsetDateTime lastUpdatedAt)
        Description copied from interface: ISyncAsset
        Sets the date, when this asset has been updated the last time.

        The last update time is not used to compare for updated content. Times seem to be too prune to different settings on servers of Smint.io and sync target. Hence all meta data of assets are updated, once Smint.io detects a change. Binary data uses a simple, increasing counter as version number (see getBinaryVersion()) which can be used to see, which binary is the newest one. Only Smint.io platform will update the binary data, though. Without a single source, increasing counter would not work as they are not unique then.

        Specified by:
        setLastUpdatedAt in interface ISyncAsset
        Parameters:
        lastUpdatedAt - the date of last update of this asset or null.
        Returns:
        this to support Fluent Interface

        ISyncBinaryAsset setLicensePurchaseTransactionUuid(String licensePurchaseTransactionUuid)
        Description copied from interface: ISyncAsset
        This is a Smint.io internal ID of the asset within the purchase.

        The value itself does not have any practical use for the user of the sync target, but is necessary to retrieve further information about the asset from the Smint.io platform. Actually, it is the same value as #getUuid() but might be changed in the future to use a different value.

        With a purchase you actually buy a license to use the asset, hence the name of this value contains "license" and "purchase transaction".

      • setHasBeenCancelled

        ISyncBinaryAsset setHasBeenCancelled(boolean hasBeenCancelled)
        Description copied from interface: ISyncAsset
        Set to true if the purchase transaction has been cancelled prior to fulfillment of payment.

        Assets are regarded as being purchased until this value is being set to true. If set to true, then the user was strongly interested in the asset but actually did not buy it. Thus no license is available to really use this asset.

        Such a situation might happen in case the asset has been already purchased in the past and therefore is managed by the sync target. Nevertheless the maximum number of usage/downloads have been reached and more must be purchased. If the purchase is being cancelled for some reason, it will be indicated by this flag.

        Specified by:
        setHasBeenCancelled in interface ISyncAsset
        Parameters:
        hasBeenCancelled - if true the purchase transaction for new licenses has been cancelled.
        Returns:
        this to support Fluent Interface

      • setIsEditorialUse

        ISyncBinaryAsset setIsEditorialUse(Boolean isEditorialUse)
        Description copied from interface: ISyncAsset
        Sets a flag that this asset can only be used for editorial use.

        Until a value has been passed to this function, it can not be determined whether the asset is for editorial use only or not. There might be some content provider that do not provide this information on some assets. It simply is impossible to tell. The default assumption and its derived legal action depends on the synchronization target. Smint.io can not give any advise how to handle such content.

        Specified by:
        setIsEditorialUse in interface ISyncAsset
        Parameters:
        isEditorialUse - Boolean.TRUE in case the asset is allowed for Editorial Use only and Boolean.FALSE if the asset can be used for Creative content, too. If this can not be determined, than null is being set.
        Returns:
        this to support Fluent Interface

      • setHasLicenseTerms

        ISyncBinaryAsset setHasLicenseTerms(boolean hasLicenseTerms)
        Description copied from interface: ISyncAsset
        Sets a flag whether this asset has license terms attached or not.

        With many sync targets the license information is being stored in an unstructured way, that its data can not be easily analyzed. Then it is hard to tell, whether license terms are applied to this asset or not. Smint.io stores all license terms in a structured way and is able to detect such terms. Hence this flag is being set by Smint.io to lift this burden from sync targets.

        Until a value has been passed to this function, assume false as default.

        Specified by:
        setHasLicenseTerms in interface ISyncAsset
        Parameters:
        hasLicenseTerms - true in case any license term/restriction applies to this asset.
        Returns:
        this to support Fluent Interface

      • setLicenseType

        ISyncBinaryAsset setLicenseType(String licenseTypeKey)
        Description copied from interface: ISyncAsset
        Sets a general type ID of the kind license applying to this asset.

        The type ID is a simple reading text, which has been defined up-front by Smint.io. Its value is arbitrary and uses mixed cases. Non-exhaustive example:

        • all - all is allowed, no restrictions are applied.
        • royalty_free - royalty free content.
        • rights_managed - rights managed content with more detailed license restrictions.
        • rights_ready

        Although a known set of values are used, some might be changed and more be added in the near future without any further notice. So implementing classes must support an arbitrary value.

        Specified by:
        setLicenseType in interface ISyncAsset
        Parameters:
        licenseTypeKey - the key of the type of license or null.
        Returns:
        this to support Fluent Interface
